                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                            <h2 class="title">What is Realistic Random Records?</h2>
                            <h5 class="description">Do you need fake user information for a presentation? &nbsp;mockup? &nbsp;logic or database testing? &nbsp;Does it need to be more realistic than "John Doe" or "asdf user1"? &nbsp;Do you need hundreds or thousands of data points and you don't have an unpaid intern that will do it by hand?</h5>
                            <h3 class="description">Then this is the API for you!</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="features">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                                <div class="info">
                                    <div class="icon icon-info">
                                        <i class="material-icons">fingerprint</i>
                                    </div>
                                    <h4 class="info-title">Realistic</h4>
                                    <p>All of the data fields are sourced from real-world historical databases such as <a href="https://www.census.gov/en.html" target="_blank">the US Census Bureau</a> and <a href="https://www.ssa.gov/" target="_blank">the US Social Security Administration</a>, as well as follow appropriate formats, conventions, and specifications.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                                <div class="info">
                                    <div class="icon icon-success">
                                        <i class="material-icons">casino</i>
                                    </div>
                                    <h4 class="info-title">Random</h4>
                                    <p>We use a weighted random algorithm so the generated results reflect real life. &nbsp;Someone born in 1980 is more likely to be named Michael than Abraham, and that probability is also reflected in our results.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                                <div class="info">
                                    <div class="icon icon-danger">
                                        <i class="material-icons">disc_full</i>
                                    </div>
                                    <h4 class="info-title">Records</h4>
                                    <p>There is no music here, so why call it records? &nbsp;It is a callback to the classic computer science term: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Record_(computer_science)" target="_blank">record</a> - a basic data structure that contains fields of information. &nbsp;And who doesn't love alliteration?</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
